\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 34. C. oporinoides} Boiss. ex Froelich in DC.,{\i  Prodr.}{\b  7}: 165 (1838). Perennial; stems 1-8, 8-50 cm, simple or divaricately branched. Leaves glabrous or with short glandular or eglandular hairs; basal 5-23 × 1-3(-5) cm, oblanceolate, acute to caudate-acuminate, narrowed at base, pinnatifid with retrorse triangular to linear, mucronate lateral lobes; cauline like the basal or bractlike. Capitula few. Involucre 9-15 × 4-10 mm; bracts linear lanceolate, obtuse, the outer c. ½ as long as inner, canescent-tomentulose, pubescent on inner face. Ligules reddish-purple on outer face. Achenes 7-9·5 mm, yellowish, fusiform, attenuate at apex, 20- to 30-ribbed. 2n = 8.{\i  Screes and rock-crevices,} 1700-3000{\i  m. • S. & S.E. Spain. }Hs.
