\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. C. sibthorpiana} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.} {\b 2}({\b 11}): 56 (1849) ({\i C. divaricata} subsp. {\i sibthorpiana} (Boiss. & Heldr.) Hayek). Perennial; stems 3-12 cm, with 3-4 short, divaricate branches. Leaves canescent-tomentose or glabrous; basal 2-6 × 0·5-1·3 cm, oblanceolate, acute to obtuse, narrowed at base, runcinate-dentate or pinnatifid, terminal segment irregular, lateral segments triangular-acute; cauline few, small, the lower like the basal or bract-like. Capitula few. Involucre 9-10 × 5-7 mm; bracts lanceolate or linear-lanceolate, obtuse, the outer c. 1/3 as long as inner, densely canescent-tomentose, pubescent on inner face. Ligules reddish-purple on outer face. Achenes 4·7-5 × 0·8 mm, brown, fusiform, slightly attenuate at apex, 10-ribbed.{\i  Mountain rocks,} 1800-2450{\i  m. • Kriti.} Cr.
