\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 38. C. guioliana} Babcock, {\i op. cit.}{\b  22}: 485 (1947). Perennial; stems 2, up to 45 cm, with up to 5 branches. Leaves sparsely canescent-tomentulose, and with minute, brown, glandular hairs; basal up to 15 × 2 cm, numerous, oblanceolate, acute or acuminate, narrowed at base, pinnately sinuate-dentate, the teeth acuminate and mucronate; lower cauline like the basal; upper cauline linear and entire. Capitula few. Involucre 10-13 × 7-12 mm; bracts linear-lanceolate to lanceolate, obtuse to acute, the outer 10-12, 1/2-2/3 as long as inner, canescent-tomentose, pubescent on inner face. Achenes c. 7 mm, yellowish-brown, fusiform, attenuate and constricted at apex, 16- to 20-ribbed. •{\i  N.W. Greece} ({\i Smolikas}). Gr.
