\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 39. C. crocifolia} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 7}): 14 (1846-1847). Perennial; stems up to 25 cm, with a few slender branches. Leaves glabrous; basal 4-8 × 0·2-0·4 cm, numerous, linear or the lowest narrowly oblanceolate, acute or somewhat obtuse, gradually narrowed to the petiole, entire; lowest cauline like the basal, the remainder remote, gradually reduced or bract-like. Capitula 1-few. Involucre c. 10 mm; bracts linear-lanceolate, acute, the outer c. 1/3 as long as inner, sparsely canescent-tomentulose. Achenes 5-5·5 × 0·6-0·7 mm, yellowish, fusiform, sometimes slightly curved, strongly attenuate at apex, c. 20-striate.{\i  Mountain rocks. • S. Greece} ({\i Taïyetos}). Gr.
