\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 40. C. athoa} Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.} {\b 2}({\b 11}): 57 (1849). Perennial; stems 1 or more, 15-35 cm, remotely branched from near the base. Leaves glabrous or tomentulose; basal 5-15 × 0·5-3 cm, numerous, oblanceolate, acute, dentate to runcinate-pinnate, with triangular, acute teeth or lobes; cauline few, linear, acute or acuminate, entire. Capitula 1-4. Involucre 9-10 × 5-7 mm; bracts linear-lanceolate, acute, the outer c. ½ as long as inner, canescent-tomentulose, pubescent on inner face. Achenes 4·4-5 × 0·5 mm, yellowish-brown, fusiform-cylindrical, c. 16-striate.{\i  Mountain rocks. • N.E. Greece} ({\i Athos}). Gr.
